M||tx|---
M|Them|tx|This skill provides a curated collection of professional font and color themes themes, each w/ carefully selected color palettes and font pairings. Once a theme is chosen, it can be applied to any artifact.
M|Purp|To a|
M|Purp|it|A cohesive color palette w/ hex codes
M|Purp|it|Complementary font pairings for headers and body text
M|Purp|it|A distinct visual identity suitable for different contexts and audiences
M|Usag|To a|
M|Usag|1. *|Display the `theme-showcase.pdf` file to allow us to see all available themes visually. Do not make any modifications to it; simply show the file for viewing.
M|Usag|2. *|Ask which theme to apply to the deck
M|Usag|3. *|Get explicit confirmation abt the chosen theme
M|Usag|4. *|Once a theme has been chosen, apply the selected theme's colors and fonts to the deck/artifact
M|Them|The |
M|Them|tx|1. **Ocean Depths** - Professional and calming maritime theme
M|Them|tx|2. **Sunset Boulevard** - Warm and vibrant sunset colors
M|Them|tx|3. **Forest Canopy** - Natural and grounded earth tones
M|Them|tx|4. **Modern Minimalist** - Clean and contemporary grayscale
M|Them|tx|5. **Golden Hour** - Rich and warm autumnal palette
M|Them|tx|6. **Arctic Frost** - Cool and crisp winter-inspired theme
M|Them|tx|7. **Desert Rose** - Soft and sophisticated dusty tones
M|Them|tx|8. **Tech Innovation** - Bold and modern tech aesthetic
M|Them|tx|9. **Botanical Garden** - Fresh and organic garden colors
M|Them|tx|10. **Midnight Galaxy** - Dramatic and cosmic deep tones
M|Them|Each|
M|Them|it|Cohesive color palette w/ hex codes
M|Them|it|Complementary font pairings for headers and body text
M|Them|it|Distinct visual identity suitable for different contexts and audiences
M|Appl|Afte|
M|Appl|tx|1. Read the corresponding theme file from the `themes/` directory
M|Appl|tx|2. Apply the specified colors and fonts consistently throughout the deck
M|Appl|tx|3. Ensure proper contrast and readability
M|Appl|tx|4. Maintain the theme's visual identity across all slides
M|Crea|tx|To handle cases where none of the existing themes work for an artifact, cr a custom theme. Based on provided inputs, gn a new theme similar to the ones above. Give the theme a similar name describing what the font/color combinations represent. Use any basic description provided to choose appropriate colors/fonts. After generating the theme, show it for rv and verification. Following that, apply the theme as described above.